mjp@austin.ibm.com (Michael Phelps) writes:
: 
....
: Actually, the Swiss goverment is much older, seems to be quite democratic, and
: (BTW) allows ownership of firearms that we can't legally own in the US.  
: 

Actually, democratic government in a modern sense is fairly young in 
Switzerland. Ownership and in particular carrying of handguns is regulated
in all Kantons (~states), in general carrying of "concealable" weapons
is not allowed without a license. It is however fairly easy to purchase 
rifles. 
